node.text: “It looks like a paper plate with a face on it!” In a new episode of our Cartoon Challenge, @aparnapkin draws a New Yorker cartoon, and drafts her very own caption, with the help of the expert @willmcphail4. Feel free to compliment her artistry in the comments below. (Do *not* mention the ghouls!)

node.title: Aparna Nancherla Tries to Keep Up With a New Yorker Cartoonist

node.text: “It looks like a paper plate with a face on it!” In a new episode of our Cartoon Challenge, @aparnapkin draws a New Yorker cartoon, and drafts her very own caption, with the help of the expert @willmcphail4. Feel free to compliment her artistry in the comments below. (Do *not* mention the ghouls!)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The New Yorker Cartoons on August 26, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'CARTON CAPTION CONTEST Contest #769 To submit your caption, leave it comment below, with the hashtag #MyNewYorkerCaption. jeRTaлR 00ย'.

node.text:
How to win friends and influence people: become a caption-contest champion, of course! Do your damndest right here on Instagram by submitting your caption in the comments below, with the hashtag #MyNewYorkerCaption.

Finalists for this week’s cartoon, by @kaamranhafeez, will appear online September 7th and in the September 13, 2021, issue of the magazine. You must be over 13 to officially enter. Only one submission with the hashtag per username is permitted. Tap the link in our bio for the full contest rules.
